This paper is about neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new framework for NMT using back-translation, which involves training a bi-directional translation model. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of pre-training, which is a common technique in deep learning, indicating that it may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) since NMT can be used for tasks such as image captioning.
